dinner conversation with joanna levitt of international accountability project center for latin american studies jump to navigation stanford university center for latin american studies search this site home events dinner conversation with joanna levitt of international accountability project dinner conversation with joanna levitt of international accountability project thursday march 1 2012 6 00pm 8 00pm perspectives on sustainable development in latin america working group invites students to converse with joanna levitt of the international accountability project over dinner a recent stanford alumna joanna levitt is now the executive director of international accountability project iap based out of san francisco iap is a group that challenges destructive development projects that uproot and impoverish millions of people across the global south working with grassroots and international partners iap advocates for international policies that respect the rights and livelihoods of people threatened by unjust development and supports communities to hold their ground and defend their homes environment and human rights prior to joining iap joanna has worked on rights to free prior informed consent fpic with the centro de derechos economicos y sociales center for economic and social rights in ecuador as a fulbright scholar and with the center for international environmental law in washington dc as a gardner fellow students will have the chance to participate in informal but engaging conversation with joanna levitt in a small setting to ask questions about her current work career path and visions for sustainable development dinner served rsvp requested to adeaconu stanford edu joanna levitt international accountability project bolivar house 582 alvarado row last updated february 22 2012 4 45pm calendar main menu about degree programs visiting faculty & scholar programs grants & fellowships people events newsletter giving to clas secondary menu stanford home ica clasp login 